summary: Veteran A came to his clinic appointment and brought a white plastic mailing envelope with his name on it with label stating VAMC Lincoln, NE 68510-2451. Inside this envelope were refill medication paper for accu-check plus a test strips for Veteran B as well as a second page listing prescriptions requested and dates when they would be mailed to him. This package was mailed 4-26-12. Veteran A kept it until he had his clinic appointment today. He reported he looked at it, knew he wasn_t using insulin test strips so thought he would just bring it with him at his next clinic apointment.

victim.victim_id: United States Department of Veterans Affairs
